Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.26,0:00:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and Luise both joined \Nthe Little Detective Agency,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.11,0:00:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,determined to get to the bottom of the reasons \Nbehind dad and mom's break-up in their investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.83,0:00:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte's investigation ultimately ended in a failure, \Nand now, let's check on Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.41,0:00:30.41,Sign,,0,0,110,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 12 \N {\fs35} The Secret Brought to Light {to determine (esp. a culprit or underlying cause); to pin down; to ascertain; to locate; to identify} {秘密をつきとめた} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h   Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.68,0:01:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad, Hans!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.75,0:01:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a talent!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.65,0:01:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans! Let it be known to Vienna, \Nits number one street performer is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.82,0:01:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.13,0:01:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Europe's number one audience! {probably 100万人 minna san but idk what he means, 100万 usually means "of all sorts/one in a million"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.33,0:01:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.86,0:01:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You play really well, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.52,0:01:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.34,0:01:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked it, too. Certainly, I'm going to send \Nmy orchestra's scouts after you, in the future. {(talent) scout; recruiter; headhunter}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.54,0:01:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mean to sound disrespectful, but I really intend \Nto be performing on the streets for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.51,0:01:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, how can I let down \Nthe town folk, my devoted fans?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.98,0:01:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll manage, accept it! {no clue what's yobitta, yobi is call; invitation​, erazo is "great" which may be both "great performance" and "great offer"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.52,0:01:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We believe in you, Hans!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.39,0:01:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is a pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.29,0:01:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, our orchestra had just suffered a loss \Nof one more musical genius. {/great artist}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.26,0:01:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My! That must be Herr Palfy! Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.78,0:01:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean the composer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.91,0:02:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for this. \NThe resemblance is striking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.72,0:02:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Luise, is our investigation \Nof your dad's affairs still ongoing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.62,0:02:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave up on it. \NIt seems, on my end, it's a nonstarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.12,0:02:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure, on Luise's end...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.52,0:02:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevermind. Ne-ver mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.63,0:02:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. You must have already \Nbrought it to light by now. {word from ep title}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.11,0:02:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As a fellow Little Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.32,0:02:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}must{\i0} get an answer out of her today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.22,0:02:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How come dad and mom ended up divorcing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.49,0:03:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Maintaining the pressure \Nis essential in such matters. {/momentum}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.24,0:03:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.17,0:03:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Not here. Not here either!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.67,0:03:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My, where else could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.98,0:03:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get anything done if I don't find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.23,0:03:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My report on business communications​! {sounds AWFULLY lot like horenso no kisshu which is a real thing - quiche with spinach, but that'd make no sense to hide in your bedroom, what the fuck, gotta be something about "manuscript/article" since it has ki, or so I thought especially since later she finds a book, but still, this coincidence is concerning, idk, maybe it's a joke about how hectic and tired she is, hiding food under her bed/calling a manuscript food?; okay, hourensou may be "reporting, contacting, and consultation​ (Business, Abbreviation, from 報告・連絡・相談)" but kisshu - still no clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.25,0:03:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I come at an unfortunate moment, \Nbut I have an important matter to... {confusion; bustle; misfortune; disorder - again, why;d you fucking apologize for interrupting that}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.43,0:03:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Found it. Here you are, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.45,0:03:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.21,0:03:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Blimey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.46,0:03:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.57,0:03:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.14,0:03:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see, Lotte, I'm busy now. \NLet's talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.17,0:03:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? It's that late already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.77,0:03:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can't get anything done in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.48,0:03:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.09,0:03:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.26,0:03:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, two women candidates stepped forward... {candidacy; standing as a candidate; bidding (to host an event, e.g. the Olympics)}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.32,0:04:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.08,0:04:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about raising your allowance again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.20,0:04:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually not!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.55,0:04:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.24,0:04:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a moment, \Nthis article just gave me an idea. {not sure what she means: this article can do to things}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.89,0:04:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough work already!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.23,0:04:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I really need to discuss this urgently!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.90,0:04:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get in a fight with Annie again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.85,0:04:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, okay? \NWe'll take our revenge later. {lit: later, in plenty}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.18,0:04:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not something that petty either! {/simple}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.13,0:04:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I need an answer right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.59,0:04:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, I need your full attention, \Nnot diverted to eating and reading news{papers}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.44,0:04:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For me, this is a matter of...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.26,0:04:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A minute of silence, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.23,0:04:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Hey, that's rude! {sly; cunning; sneaky; crafty; unfair; dishonest​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you didn't eat your carrot again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.26,0:04:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Go finish it, it's nutritious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.27,0:04:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You leave some milk in your cup every time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.70,0:04:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, you make me drink mine while gagging me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.42,0:04:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In any discussion, grown-ups do the speaking,\Nkids do the listening. {I think she means "whatever is the matter, it's good for adults [to speak], but it's bad for kids"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.33,0:04:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, the grown-ups are convinced, the rest of the world \Nis supposed to cater to their needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.31,0:04:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.13,0:04:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this kind of talk, \Nin return for my patient listening? {no clue what she means: How dare you talk to me like that if you just shut up and listen/if you listen silently, what is this mouth's way of asking​/listening?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.37,0:04:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But mom, you're always...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.74,0:04:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a word more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.95,0:05:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Any more complaints?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.66,0:05:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.03,0:05:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A grown-up is someone who has to constantly consider \Nboth his own affairs and his child's ones. {lit: those called adults, think about things in the world and children}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.43,0:05:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The need to work hard for the success of those \Nis what warrants such conduct.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.44,0:05:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.64,0:05:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Adults are those who prefer to turn a blind eye to it \Nover conceding the inconvenient truth before the children. {/hide from the children whatever they find inconvenient}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.54,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope. I never turn a blind eye \Nto anything you bring up. {/not hiding anything from lotte}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.63,0:05:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me then!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.92,0:05:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.66,0:05:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.13,0:05:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you two break up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.09,0:06:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason we should discuss this. {hitsuyo?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.91,0:06:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But you said you'll face anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.82,0:06:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.29,0:06:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Please understand that mom \Nhas her own mom matters to tend to.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.44,0:06:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing this for you, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.75,0:06:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a thing of that is actually for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.64,0:06:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate you, mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.41,0:06:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A mom like that just can't be my mom. {unsure, maybe she means "you don't deserve to be ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.83,0:06:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.44,0:07:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This mom is no longer qualified \Nto be Lotte's mom. {/stops being ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.97,0:07:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm living in the office, starting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.11,0:07:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can ask Cleopatra, Queen Elizabeth, or whoever it is you prefer more...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.60,0:07:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to be your mom! {/choose ... or anyone you like as ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.48,0:07:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.12,0:07:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was I so sharp... {/rude/cruel}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.83,0:08:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.86,0:08:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This all spiraled out of control. {/this is not what i intended}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.89,0:08:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the kind of world we're living in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.07,0:08:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the grown-ups are pretty uptight \Nwhen it comes to the reasons for their divorce. {/reluctant}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.58,0:08:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not at all surprising that you quarreled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.71,0:08:15.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,You're pretty well-informed on marriages, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.18,0:08:16.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:22.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,It's just that when the others only ever bully you, \Nyou start pondering on intricacies of life merely to kill time. {hopefully she means this, lit: a bullied kid like me has no choice but to think profoundly about the life}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.31,0:08:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't envy you. {trouble; hardship; difficulty; labour; labor; toil; pains}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.15,0:08:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! I should introduce you \Nto a "Benevolent Person."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.82,0:08:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"Benevolent person?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.99,0:08:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One Elderly Herr, and a source of my wisdom. {/who is teaching me life - I don't suppose he is teaching her directly/himself}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.63,0:08:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He is a friend of a friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.36,0:08:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And he also runs an advice column in a periodical. {lit: in journal, he has serialized life-counseling}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.06,0:08:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,His pen name is Friedrich. {she says something like furedorichi and in japanese Friedrich would be furidorihi but I don't suppose they meant someone was actually names frederichi or whtaever it is}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.33,0:08:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever Annie is harassing me again, \NI address his column for an advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.57,0:08:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll find a remedy for Lotte's plight, too! {/you can ask him about your trouble; troubles; worry; distress; sorrows; anguish; agony; problem}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.91,0:08:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What are those lousy manuscripts?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.68,0:08:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't make heads or tails of any of this! {what you wrote - I not in the least (with neg. verb); not at all understand}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.72,0:09:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Rewrite all from scratch!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't let your rebel views get in the way! {hoewever much resistance; opposition; standing up to you do - not sure what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.16,0:09:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Missis... No, Miss Körner!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.72,0:09:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my bad, Editor-in-Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.13,0:09:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll rewrite it at once. Will be done by tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.16,0:09:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.52,0:09:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hungry, aren't you? {let's go home}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.38,0:10:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,House No. 123.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.87,0:10:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.18,0:10:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's open. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.10,0:10:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.53,0:10:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.20,0:10:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where Herr Editor lives? {/...'s home}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.40,0:10:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you tell it's not a janitor's shack? {big man; boss; buddy; mate}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.11,0:10:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.87,0:11:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, Herr Friedrich is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.94,0:11:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In our line of arbeiten, \Nwe use pen names sometimes. {part-time job; side job}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.54,0:11:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's more surprising here is you - \Nvisiting me as a customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.27,0:11:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Please. I need your help with my plight. {listen to my trouble; troubles; worry; distress; sorrows; anguish; agony; problem}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.07,0:11:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've nobody else to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.75,0:11:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I finally know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.56,0:11:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure came here \Nwith a quite the quandary on your hands. {to have (problems, debts, etc.); to take on (a responsibility); to be burdened with (e.g. care of a family member); to have (children, etc.) to provide for}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.93,0:11:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you don't mind me having a bit of wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.89,0:11:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do grown-ups \Nalways drink stuff that's so bitter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.77,0:11:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. That's a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.01,0:11:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As you grow up, the reality makes you acquire a certain taste \Nfor the things that are rather bitter, don't you think? {unsure what he means: when become an adult, even in life you'll get to know a bit of bitter taste}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.75,0:11:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A taste for bitterness?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.68,0:11:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Like dreams that you have to leave behind,{/lost}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.95,0:11:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or like a mutual feeling, that you're forced to forgo, \Ndespite your best effort. {/or when you love someone, but have to part whatever you do}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.16,0:11:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a sip of this bitterness \Nhelps you forget it a little sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.56,0:11:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, that's the kind of memories \Nyour mother has about your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.10,0:12:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I had... asked her something I shouldn't have asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.34,0:12:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, mom is never going to forgive me for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.28,0:12:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She threw at me, "Go find yourself a new mom, then!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.82,0:12:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.51,0:12:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,New moms are always mean to their new children! \NThe one in Hänsel and Gretel sure was! {hope this is what she means by "new mom is decided at mean/bullying"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.19,0:12:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.46,0:12:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not a soul in this world \Nwho wouldn't love our little Fraulein Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.93,0:12:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't work! Because I myself \Nwon't be able to love any mom other than my own! {unsure, maybe "i will no longer be loved by my mom"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.60,0:12:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, this must be your mother \Nwho came to hand in the manuscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.06,0:12:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? This is bad. \NShe doesn't want to see me now. What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.28,0:12:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not home, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.75,0:12:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No... No!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.78,0:12:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.72,0:12:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, the manuscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.36,0:13:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.07,0:13:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,See you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.03,0:13:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.33,0:13:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I may... need your advice on one more matter. {/consultation}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.70,0:13:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So what was it you needed help with?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.50,0:13:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to ask about Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.64,0:13:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, up until now, \NI have never talked to her about her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.74,0:13:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought this would spare \Nher little heart some undue worry. {/expressly; especially; specially; taking the trouble (to do); going to the trouble of (doing); going out of one's way (to do)​ to not hurt ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.55,0:13:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet... I still hurt her this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.78,0:13:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I'm starting to question this decision. {unsure, prolly she means "it was a mistake what I did this morning"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.93,0:13:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as she said. \NI guess, I really am a whimsical grown-up. {selfish; self-centred; egotistical}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.87,0:13:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.94,0:13:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My... Were you already receiving someone before me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.09,0:13:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Ah... No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.21,0:14:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So sorry! Such matters should not be your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.55,0:14:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best that I have my leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.02,0:14:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Miss Körner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.26,0:14:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.16,0:14:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.23,0:14:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You okay, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.42,0:14:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.95,0:14:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Well, well... Ah... You two...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.75,0:14:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Lotte sure is adorable!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.88,0:14:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And... Miss Körner is always in her best shape, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.29,0:14:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Care to join me for some wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.90,0:14:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A taste for bitterness, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.84,0:16:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What now? Giving up already? {I'm beaten; I give up​ - unsure what she implies by that}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.84,0:16:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I never give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.82,0:16:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.43,0:16:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.93,0:16:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Up until this day, I was avoiding \Ntalking to you about your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.99,0:16:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.09,0:16:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.71,0:16:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. I'm not mad anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.97,0:16:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I now know that even my bitter memories \Ncan be turned to joy if I share them with you. {unsure what she means: mom's paiful feelings, to be understood by you is a happy material - is this about what bernau told lotte about how adult life is bitter or something? but mom's not supposed to know it}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.35,0:16:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father is a gifted musician.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,However, by the time we two married \Nhe wasn't yet enjoying even a fraction of his current fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.50,0:17:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, day after day, in front of the piano, \Nhe was composing, as if in a daze. {/obsessed}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.26,0:17:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I was also offering a prayer daily
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.18,0:17:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,for your dad's passion and talent to be rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.01,0:17:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, one day, this wish came true, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.14,0:17:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.78,0:17:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.35,0:17:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when the fame found your father,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.96,0:17:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it became even worse: day after day, after day, \Nhe worked away in the atelier. "I'm busy, busy, busy!" {/work, work} {/he started sharply in atelier}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, he stopped coming home altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.94,0:17:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That was when I decided \Nthe time has come to have my leave. {/ran off from home}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.45,0:17:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Soon after, people from all around the globe \Nbecame profoundly awed by your father's talent. {/became an artist beloved in all world}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.92,0:17:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, so be it. {i dunno what she means by "can't be helped" here - nothing bad happened, why should it be helped? can't be helped that she left him before he became famous? what the fuck does that change?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.96,0:18:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, the best way to make another happy \Nis to rid them of your presence. {lit: mutually, without yourself is the way of happiness for your partner}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.56,0:18:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is also a form of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.24,0:18:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Between you and dad, who is to blame? {/which one is guilty}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.27,0:18:16.21,Sign,,0,0,0,,Neither is to blame here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.72,0:18:19.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,We were both merely trying \Nto get the best out of our lives. {hope she means this by "living with all our might"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.85,0:18:22.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,It's a bit hard to comprehend,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.07,0:18:24.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,but aren't you sad about it? {sad; miserable; unhappy; sorrowful​}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.57,0:18:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in the slightest!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.01,0:18:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm confident - \Ntomorrow will always be better than today. {hopefully this is what she means by "more than yesterday, love tomorrow more" alghough I suspect it may be "I'll love you more tomorrow than I did yesterday" or soemthing}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.95,0:18:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There would also be sad days, sure, \Nbut with enough hard work, you can make them good, too! {lit: there are sad things too, but a hard labor can turn them into great things}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.63,0:18:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think it's the same for your dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.50,0:18:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For dad, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.36,0:18:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, he'll keep making great music \Nwith unrelenting passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.53,0:18:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You father is primarily a composer,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.53,0:18:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,known to the world as a virtuous gentleman, {world; society; people; the public say he is an elegant; refined; polished; stylish; sophisticated gentleman}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.70,0:18:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but also as a conceited featherbrain. {careless person; scatterbrain; birdbrain; hasty person at conceit; vanity; pride; self-importance; egotism}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.55,0:18:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right, an easygoing fellow! {shiterushi?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.41,0:18:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.45,0:19:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he totally should be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.99,0:19:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, hey, he's my dad, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.32,0:19:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that'd make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.33,0:19:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's cold! Let's hurry. Let's hurry home!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.39,0:19:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.21,0:19:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.43,0:19:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you understand, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.91,0:19:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not overly concerned \Nabout who exactly your father is. {very unsure what she means, maybe "I'm glad you didn't make me tell you who..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.08,0:19:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.75,0:19:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you. Now I know for sure. {/for telling me}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.30,0:19:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, the reason for dad and mom's break-up \Nwas brought to light in all the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.60,0:20:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Both dad and mom \Nboth turned out to be the most amazing grown-ups. {no clue what he means: both/each look like great adults}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.15,0:20:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"The way things stand now, \None day, they very much might reconcile," {/start getting along}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.57,0:20:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so thought Luise in that moment of happiness.
Comment: 0,0:20:20.27,0:20:20.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.21,0:20:29.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.74,0:20:33.20,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.20,0:20:36.92,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.92,0:20:39.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:51.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.47,0:20:55.23,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.23,0:20:58.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.77,0:21:02.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.61,0:21:05.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.19,0:21:08.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.74,0:21:13.29,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.29,0:21:17.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.99,0:21:22.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.64,0:21:26.05,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams: {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.05,0:21:29.68,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.68,0:21:32.45,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.50,0:21:37.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.27,0:21:40.68,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, I'll do my best to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:44.27,0:21:44.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.61,0:21:46.05,Sign,,0,0,0,,In the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.58,0:21:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We two have switched places!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.65,0:21:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, this is bad! \NWe're having a gym class tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.26,0:21:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But because I'm not actually Luise, \NI can't do neither the horizontal bar, nor athletics!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.62,0:21:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, try to make it through, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.29,0:22:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All hope's lost now! Moreover, Truda is starting \Nto question whether or not I may be Lotte. {to doubt; to distrust; to be suspicious of; to suspect}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.09,0:22:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, we must do our utmost to protect our secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.63,0:22:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best, Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.74,0:22:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, I don't think I'll be able to protect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.47,0:22:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.11,0:22:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte's Quandary!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.11,0:22:14.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 13 \NLotte's Quandary!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.67,0:22:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to it!
